07/10/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu on Wednesday (6 October) urged the justice and public order structures to step up the fight against crime and corruption. 
During his meeting with Interior Minister Igli Toska, Justice Minister Fatmir Xhafaj, Prosecutor-General Theodhori Sollaku and other judiciary officials, Moisiu called for more professionalism and commitment from all public order institutions. 
He noted that crime is increasing along with reported cases of corruption. 
He acknowledged that international organisations are correct in saying laws are not fully enforced in all parts of the country. 
(Albanian Daily News - 07/10/04; ATA - 06/10/04)
